race.comment: ROONAMI (13) was Canberra and then was backed off the map at Wagga and was well beaten into a place after settling last and meeting trouble. Peaks for this and Penza stays aboard. She can settle close today and the step up to the mile is ideal. BEAUTY SWIFT (6) was an easy trial winner at Hawkesbury before his 2L defeat here over 1400m on debut. Jumped an equal 4.0 equal-favourite and is sure to have come on. Should enjoy the mile and can make the finish. ATTESTOR (1) just missed here two back but was plain at Hawkesbury following. He's capable of using the inside barrier and forgiving the latest has each way claims. Collett rides PRESUMPTUOUS GAL (12) and quick improvement is likely. Didn't have the best of it at  Newcastle on debut, and she maps for the run of the race. Keep a close eye on the late betting.
